A new case of coronavirus recorded in Al-Ahsa and 3 [deaths] in the Eastern Region
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Within the framework of the epidemiological surveillance of the novel coronavirus (MERS-CoV), the Ministry of Health (MOH) has announced that a new Saudi citizen, aged 61 who suffers from kidney failure and other chronic diseases, has been recorded to be infected with coronavirus in the Al-Ahsa Region, bringing the total number of the infected people with this virus to 38 cases.

Furthermore, MOH has announced the death of 3 cases, who had been previously announced to be infected with this virus and admitted to hospital about a month ago. It is noteworthy that all of these cases, ranging in age from 60,58 and 24 years, have chronic kidney failure and other diseases.

