[The newswire above containing information from an interview with the deputy minister of public health mentions the new cluster of cases in another part of the Eastern Province might represent another nosocomial cluster, with cases in the cluster all attending the same healthcare facility (different from the one in Al-Ahsa).

The other important information is that the incubation period may likely be more than 10 days. According to the French experience, the incubation period may have been 12 days, whereas the Saudis have observed incubation periods up to 14.5 days. - Mod.MPP]
